Class PairSet<T,I>

java.lang.Object

Type Parameters:
T - transaction type

All Implemented Interfaces:
java.lang.Iterable<Pair<T,I>>, java.util.Collection<Pair<T,I>>, java.util.Set<Pair<T,I>>
public class PairSet<T,I>
extends java.util.AbstractSet<Pair<T,I>>

This class can be used to represent a set of transactions.

It can be seen as a binary matrix, where rows are transactions, columns are the items involved with each transaction.

The matrix is internally represented by a bitmap defined by putting rows (transactions) in sequence. All the provided constructors allows to specify if the bitmap should be compressed (via ConciseSet) or plain (via FastSet).
